## Project

This project is originally from https://github.com/mskcc/vcf2maf

## What I did.

I modified docker and added docker-compose yaml to make it an image that can 
be used by my own project (SNS101Seq).

## PLEASE DON'T update this folder (??)

# Files:

Dockerfile: has been modified by me on 12/17/2024.
        In this one, the original making is to make use of clearlinux and 
        then install the clearlinux again to a folder, which is then copied to
        the minimal image (SCRATCH) and also install conda and necessary packages under it 
        which are then copied to the new system to a system folder, /usr/local.
        this way is to keep the image smaller. 
        
        Note that the conda itself is not working, since conda itself is installed to the
        builder image, and its all installed package do work and copied to the 
        docker container. Again, conda is installed to /usr/ folder, but not copied to
        the container. 
        
        A very good strategy. need to follow.
        
        The caveat is that when we try to install R on clearlinux. the container grows too big,
        bigger than other system (ubuntu or debian) containers. Need to keep eyes on this.
        
        
        
Dockerfile.orig: this is the one originally from the repo. 

docker-compose.yaml: I added on 12/17/2024. need to modified the mapping of folder to connect to
    different real folder for data and reference sequences.

